cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of registering RGB-D images from a hand-held camera into a globally consistent 3D model, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that leverages robust registrations at finer scales to seed detection and enforcement of new correspondence and structural constraints at coarser scales, which involves optimization and graph-based methods, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper provides a benchmark with manually-clicked point correspondences, which involves data analysis and evaluation, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
